{
  "answer": "**The *Viṣṇu Smṛti* (also known as Vishnu Smriti) lists the eight kinds of marriage (*vivāha*) in Chapter 24, verses 17–18.**\n\nThere, it states:\n\n> Now, there are eight forms of marriage. // Vi_24.17 //[^1]  \n> The Brāhma, Daiva, Ārṣa, Prājāpatya, Gāndharva, Āsura, Rākṣasa, and Paiśāca. // Vi_24.18 //[^2]\n\nThe text then briefly defines each form in the following verses (24.19–26) and notes that the first four (Brāhma through Prājāpatya) are righteous, while the Gāndharva is also approved for Kṣatriyas (24.27–28).[^3]\n\n[^1]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24, paragraph p-5a5a7f](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/#p-5a5a7f).\n\n[^2]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24, paragraph p-3a34b6](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/#p-3a34b6).\n\n[^3]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/).",
